parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the engine slows down
the check engine light appears
the vehicle hesitates
and the vehicle stalls at idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light appears
the engine light is constantly coming on
the ignition coil/fuel injection system fails
the wiring harness fails
and the catalytic converter fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission and motor mount issues can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transaxle jumps out of place
the vehicle crashes
the motor mounts are defective
and the vehicle vibrates and hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Sensors and On-Board Diagnostic System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty sensors and on-board diagnostic system can cause the check engine light to appear, leading to unnecessary repairs and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The check engine light appears due to a loose fuel filler cap
the mass air flow sensor is loose
and the on-board diagnostic system is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or slip gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
loses power
or slips gears; transmission warning lights appear on the dashboard; difficulty shifting gears; clunking or rumbling sounds when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shift issues can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Gear shift won't stay in park; vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly; difficulty shifting gears; gear shift feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; clutch pedal sticks to the floor; difficulty shifting gears; vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical malfunctions can cause various systems to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Electrical malfunctions
such as faulty door locks
horn
or spark plugs; warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection to mitigate the impact of the collision.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the airbag system may not be adequate to deploy the airbags in certain crash scenarios, leading to a lack of protection for the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants. The airbag system may not be designed to deploy in certain crash scenarios
such as low-speed crashes or crashes at an angle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Airbag Deployment in Low-Speed Crashes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbags may not deploy in low-speed crashes, which can still result in serious injuries or fatalities to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a low-speed crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of brakes, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel cylinder can cause brake fluid to leak, leading to a loss of brakes, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
brake fluid leaks onto the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of brakes, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
brake fluid leaks onto the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn or warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side when braking, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side when braking
the brakes make a screeching or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose traction and slide, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle slides or loses traction when braking
the ABS warning light comes on.
